Tags.ImageDescription: The Bluenose is a bit of a Canadian icon; it's featured been featured on the dime for years. The original Bluenose was a fishing ship that won the prestigous International Fisherman's Cup. It met an ignominious fate, sinking off the coast of Haiti as a decript shadow of its former self. The replica Bluenose II was launched in 1963 as a promotion for Schooner Lager by Oland Brewery.
